page.title: 01N.Sevenoaks, Seal & Kemsing
page.content: This is a residential area on the north edge of Sevenoaks merging into farmland and woodland. The 19th.C.{Bat and Ball} station is so called because the former industry, manufacturing cricket bats and balls attracted commuters to the area. {Seal} is an old picturesque village on the old Saxon road (now A25) from Winchester to Maidstone. {Kemsing} is a typical Downland Pilgrim's Way village with a church and well of interest. There is a Youth Hostel there. There are many former gravel pits now filled with water and used in a variety of ways - Nature Reserve, Water sports and park. There is a small modern industrial estate, supporting light industry.
